Gov. Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano State, on Sunday, condoled with the families of 17 men who lost their lives in a motor accident along Kano-Zaria highway, on Saturday. The condolence was conveyed in a press statement signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Abba Anwar, and made available to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Kano. “Their death came to us as very shocking. This is a great loss not only to their families or to the people of Sani Mainagge, in Gwale local government area, where they came from, but to all of us, the government and the people of Kano state. “The incident is an act of Allah alone; only He can forgive them. We are, therefore, praying to Allah Almighty to grant them Jannatul Fiddaus. May He forgive their wrongdoings and may He give their families the fortitude to bear the loss,” Ganduje said.On behalf of the government and people of the state, Ganduje commiserated with the families, people of Sani Mainagge, Gwale local government, their friends and relations over the sad incident, the statement said.  (NAN) By Muhammad Nur Tijani Kano - Gov. Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano State has described the death of the former governor of Oyo State, Sen. Abiola Ajimobi, as shocking and devastating. The condolence is contained in a statement signed by the Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Malam Abba Anwar, on… In "Politics" At least,16 travelers and residents of Dambatta Local Government Area of Kano State have died after being shot by bandits. According to Sahara Reporters, the victims were killed on Wednesday along Abuja-Kaduna expressway on their way back to Kano from a business trip to Abuja. Governor Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano… In "Politics" By Muhammad Nur Tijani   Kano  - ‎Gov. Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano State has sympathised with families of recent flood victims in the state, assuring them of state governments support.‎ Ganduje’s sympathy is contained in a statement issued by his Chief Press Secretary, Malam Abba Anwar in Kano on Tuesday.… In "News"